The White House Press Secretary, Jay Carney, provided a briefing on December 14, 2012, addressing multiple topics. He started by informing the press that President Obama was notified of the shooting at a school in Newtown, Connecticut, and was receiving regular updates on the incident. Carney then answered questions about the President's thoughts on the shooting, the legalization of marijuana, the fiscal cliff negotiations, entitlement programs, and the appointment of a new Secretary of State. He also discussed the signing of the PNTR (Permanent Normal Trade Relations) bill with Russia and the issue of transparency in the government. Carney concluded by stating that the President recently spoke with FBI Director Mueller and Governor Malloy of Connecticut regarding the shooting.